metadata.subject: Boothbay Absolute Return Strategies, LP Q4 2016 Performance Report
metadata.sender: Ari Glass, Managing Member, Boothbay Fund Management LLC

analysis.purpose: To report Q4 2016 and full-year 2016 investment performance to investors and provide market commentary
analysis.significance: Detailed performance report for a hedge fund showing strategy performance during challenging market conditions

notable_quotes: While we consider earning +3.84% to be disappointing for our strategy on an absolute return basis, doing so with a maximum drawdown of 1.4%, and in what was a challenging environment for low-net exposure relative value strategies, leaves us viewing 2016 as a 'good' bad year.
Platform Beta is a term we have heard used to describe the overlap of long and short positions, across some of the largest market-neutral, multi-manager hedge fund managers.
We expect the Trump Presidency, additional interest rate hikes by the Fed, and global geopolitical catalysts (e.g. elections, referendums) in 2017 to contribute to a rise in market volatility.

blackmail_indicators.description: No indicators of blackmail or coercion found - this is a standard investment performance report

illegal_activity.description: No illegal activity discussed - this is a legitimate investment performance report with standard financial disclosures

details: References to financial media describing 2016 as 'among the worst years for multi-manager multi-strategy firms'

public_knowledge.context: This appears to be a confidential investment performance report sent to fund investors, not intended for public distribution

analysis.summary: This is a Q4 2016 performance report for Boothbay Absolute Return Strategies hedge fund, reporting a +0.04% return for the quarter and +3.84% for the full year, with detailed analysis of their investment strategy, risk management, and market outlook including expectations for increased volatility under the Trump administration.
